# Normalize line endings in the git index, but leave working-tree files
# alone so Obsidian / IDEs writing CRLF on Windows do not show up as
# phantom-modified in `git status`. `text` (without eol=lf) tells git
# "this is a text file — store LF in the index, write whatever the
# platform prefers in the working tree". This eliminates the flip-flop
# without forcing one convention on every editor.
*.md text
*.json text
*.ts text
*.tsx text
*.js text
*.mjs text
*.css text
